) { context in","    Text(context.date.description)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The timeline view updates its content at the start date, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"again at dates separated in time by the interval amount, which is every"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"three seconds in the example above. For a start date in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"past, the view updates immediately, providing as context the date"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding to the most recent interval boundary. The view then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"refreshes normally at subsequent interval boundaries. For a start date"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in the future, the view updates once with the current date, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"begins regular updates at the start date."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The schedule defines the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/PeriodicTimelineSchedule\/Entries"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"structure to return the sequence of dates when the timeline view calls","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/PeriodicTimelineSchedule\/entries(from:mode:)"},{"text":" method.","type":"text"}]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A schedule for updating a timeline view at regular intervals."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/PeriodicTimelineSchedule"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/PeriodicTimelineSchedule\/periodic(from:by